SOurce: Youtube - FreeCodeCamp

q: what is git?
a: free version control system

q: what is version control?
a: essentially saving and managing multiple versions of our code and information

q: what is a repository?
a: it's like a folder where your project is kept.


set-up git for cloning a repo:

shashwat@lubuntu:~/Desktop/repos$ git config --global user.name "torpidsnake"
shashwat@lubuntu:~/Desktop/repos$ git config --global user.email "forwardtoshashwat@gmail.com"
shashwat@lubuntu:~/Desktop/repos$ git config --list
user.name=torpidsnake
user.email=forwardtoshashwat@gmail.com

set your classic token at https://github.com/settings/tokens

now clone the repo by git clone https://{TOKEN}@github.com/{USERNAME}/{REPO}.git

how to set-up ssh key?
to-do

undo staging (git add . is undo-ed here)
git reset or git reset filename

undo commit (git commit is undo-ed here)
git reset HEAD~1

git log (reverse chronological order -> see all logs)

also, you can reset to a specific hash value in git log -> git reset hashvalue

